1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,333
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,333 --> 00:00:02,700
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:04,159 --> 00:00:06,795
Well, look who it is. Come in.

4
00:00:07,024 --> 00:00:08,253
Please stay seated.

5
00:00:08,796 --> 00:00:12,085
I heard you've been quite ill.
How are you feeling?

6
00:00:12,639 --> 00:00:15,355
I'm all better now. Here, have a seat.

7
00:00:20,680 --> 00:00:24,195
I remembered how much
you enjoyed the oxtail soup last time,

8
00:00:24,195 --> 00:00:25,437
so I made some for you.

9
00:00:25,937 --> 00:00:29,213
I hope it helps you regain
a little strength.

10
00:00:29,692 --> 00:00:31,485
You didn't have to go to all that trouble.

11
00:00:31,900 --> 00:00:35,392
Making oxtail soup at home
is so much work.

12
00:00:35,991 --> 00:00:36,991
Not at all.

13
00:00:38,165 --> 00:00:40,013
You said you'd found the person
you were looking for that day.

14
00:00:41,242 --> 00:00:42,579
I guess it wasn't them.

15
00:00:42,953 --> 00:00:43,953
No.

16
00:00:44,587 --> 00:00:47,467
I really thought
we'd finally meet this time.

17
00:00:51,559 --> 00:00:52,659
I almost forgot.

18
00:00:55,077 --> 00:00:57,896
I should've returned this right away.

19
00:00:58,434 --> 00:00:59,984
Thank you so much
for what you did that day.

20
00:01:00,393 --> 00:01:02,323
You didn't have to return this.

21
00:01:05,609 --> 00:01:07,717
I'm hesitant to say this, but...

22
00:01:09,723 --> 00:01:12,467
if two people are meant to meet,
no matter how far apart they are,

23
00:01:12,766 --> 00:01:14,266
they'll find each other eventually.

24
00:01:15,376 --> 00:01:17,864
And if they're not meant to,
they can be face-to-face...

25
00:01:17,864 --> 00:01:19,547
and still not recognize one another.

26
00:01:20,717 --> 00:01:24,120
Seeing how much you miss that person,

27
00:01:24,120 --> 00:01:27,003
I'm sure they're waiting for the day...

28
00:01:27,003 --> 00:01:28,301
they can meet you too.

29
00:01:28,933 --> 00:01:31,059
Do you really think so?

30
00:01:31,811 --> 00:01:33,200
Of course.

31
00:01:33,200 --> 00:01:36,557
So please regain your strength
and start searching again.

32
00:01:37,317 --> 00:01:38,901
Then, when you finally meet,

33
00:01:38,901 --> 00:01:41,571
you can make up
for all the time you've lost.

34
00:01:42,500 --> 00:01:45,700
Okay. I'll get better soon.

35
00:01:49,737 --> 00:01:51,493
What do they have so much to talk about?

36
00:01:51,680 --> 00:01:53,133
She said she'd just say hello.

37
00:01:57,299 --> 00:01:59,947
I'm really glad to see
the Chairman doing much better...

38
00:02:00,320 --> 00:02:03,112
than you said he was.

39
00:02:04,357 --> 00:02:07,207
Sometimes even I wonder...

40
00:02:07,207 --> 00:02:08,851
if a miracle has really happened.

41
00:02:09,432 --> 00:02:13,333
Of course.
Keep believing a miracle will come,

42
00:02:13,436 --> 00:02:14,835
and get well soon.

43
00:02:15,637 --> 00:02:17,624
Just hearing that gives me strength.

44
00:02:18,477 --> 00:02:22,285
Listen to me, keeping a guest here
and talking only about myself.

45
00:02:22,888 --> 00:02:24,613
What happened with your daughter?

46
00:02:25,323 --> 00:02:27,472
Did you ask her why she dropped out?

47
00:02:27,472 --> 00:02:30,848
Yes. It turns out
it was all because of my own greed.

48
00:02:31,600 --> 00:02:34,664
I thought I was doing everything I could
for my children,

49
00:02:35,181 --> 00:02:38,267
but to them, my expectations...

50
00:02:38,629 --> 00:02:40,795
must have felt like a heavy burden.

51
00:02:40,843 --> 00:02:44,501
So I just accepted it as it was.

52
00:02:44,931 --> 00:02:46,831
That was the right thing to do.

53
00:02:48,381 --> 00:02:51,411
You must've suffered a lot over it.

54
00:02:51,411 --> 00:02:53,384
Please speak casually to me now.

55
00:02:53,936 --> 00:02:56,707
I don't know where to put myself
when you're that polite.

56
00:02:58,861 --> 00:03:00,645
What's so amusing?

57
00:03:00,881 --> 00:03:02,533
This is unbelievable.

58
00:03:14,925 --> 00:03:16,245
Did your conversation go well?

59
00:03:17,205 --> 00:03:20,501
I was just about to knock
and join you two.

60
00:03:21,627 --> 00:03:25,139
What were you talking about for so long?

61
00:03:25,632 --> 00:03:28,093
Just this and that. Life in general.

62
00:03:29,396 --> 00:03:30,859
I couldn't even offer you a cup of tea.

63
00:03:31,448 --> 00:03:33,669
Since you're here, stay for lunch.

64
00:03:34,075 --> 00:03:37,051
No thanks.
I have a lot to do when I get back.

65
00:03:37,051 --> 00:03:38,571
That's right, Mother.

66
00:03:38,571 --> 00:03:41,931
She runs a real estate office.
She has to get back to work.

67
00:03:42,803 --> 00:03:46,725
You're a licensed realtor?
That's impressive.

68
00:03:47,033 --> 00:03:49,440
I heard it's not easy
to get that certification.

69
00:03:49,760 --> 00:03:50,797
It's nothing.

70
00:03:52,024 --> 00:03:54,600
Once I'm feeling better,
I'll cook for you.

71
00:03:54,600 --> 00:03:56,435
Come visit with Jeong Ran.

72
00:03:56,723 --> 00:03:58,208
Thank you, ma'am.

73
00:04:00,343 --> 00:04:01,343
Where's Father?

74
00:04:01,827 --> 00:04:04,387
He went out to the garden for a walk.

75
00:04:05,323 --> 00:04:07,336
Then I should get going.

76
00:04:07,490 --> 00:04:10,432
Ms. Kang,
could I speak with you for a moment?

77
00:04:11,212 --> 00:04:12,212
Sorry?

78
00:04:13,656 --> 00:04:16,900
I'm going out to the garden.
You two talk before you leave.

79
00:04:18,067 --> 00:04:19,067
Ma'am.

80
00:04:19,803 --> 00:04:22,134
You shouldn't catch a cold
when you're still weak.

81
00:04:22,134 --> 00:04:24,421
Why don't you put on a jacket
before you go outside?

82
00:04:25,600 --> 00:04:27,400
Thank you. I will.

83
00:04:32,947 --> 00:04:35,683
What did you talk about for so long?

84
00:04:37,224 --> 00:04:40,619
Just whether she was feeling all right,

85
00:04:41,253 --> 00:04:43,456
and about our children.

86
00:04:43,580 --> 00:04:45,800
Children? Which children?

87
00:04:46,744 --> 00:04:49,080
Don't tell me you talked about my husband.

88
00:04:49,317 --> 00:04:51,217
No, we talked about my daughter.

89
00:04:51,531 --> 00:04:53,619
How does Mother even know your daughter?

90
00:04:54,035 --> 00:04:57,283
And are you that close with her?

91
00:04:57,840 --> 00:05:00,440
I told you we'd met by chance before.

92
00:05:01,423 --> 00:05:03,875
At the time, I was having a hard time
because of my daughter.

93
00:05:06,350 --> 00:05:08,853
Why? Do you want to hear the details?

94
00:05:09,363 --> 00:05:11,579
Forget it. It's not like I'm curious.

95
00:05:12,440 --> 00:05:14,700
By the way, Ms. Kang,

96
00:05:14,859 --> 00:05:16,347
what's your deal with France?

97
00:05:17,153 --> 00:05:18,153
Sorry?

98
00:05:18,669 --> 00:05:21,563
You seem to speak French pretty well,

99
00:05:21,696 --> 00:05:24,608
and you're always acting as if you know
all about French desserts and such.

100
00:05:28,107 --> 00:05:30,744
Did you live in France or something?

101
00:05:31,700 --> 00:05:35,229
Me? In France?

102
00:05:35,832 --> 00:05:36,932
I guess not.

103
00:05:37,968 --> 00:05:40,856
You don't exactly give off a French vibe.

104
00:05:44,539 --> 00:05:47,261
And what exactly is a French vibe?

105
00:05:48,248 --> 00:05:49,893
Don't you know what a Parisienne is?

106
00:05:51,176 --> 00:05:54,821
Someone chic and elegant.

107
00:05:57,348 --> 00:05:58,348
You're not really that...

108
00:05:59,346 --> 00:06:01,883
Then why were you acting
like you knew so much?

109
00:06:03,721 --> 00:06:06,555
I think I've hurt your feelings
quite a bit.

110
00:06:07,547 --> 00:06:08,608
I apologize.

111
00:06:09,571 --> 00:06:11,013
Let's get along from now on.

112
00:06:11,155 --> 00:06:13,147
I'm not saying this
because I want an apology.

113
00:06:13,470 --> 00:06:16,397
And why would we need to get along?

114
00:06:17,075 --> 00:06:20,560
People have different classes in life.
Grades.

115
00:06:21,029 --> 00:06:22,480
There's a saying, isn't there?

116
00:06:22,620 --> 00:06:25,720
Birds of a feather flock together,
and everyone has their own circle.

117
00:06:26,531 --> 00:06:28,136
You're right.

118
00:06:29,040 --> 00:06:30,107
You, Min Ho's...

119
00:06:31,336 --> 00:06:35,013
I mean, Madam,
we're obviously from different worlds.

120
00:06:36,058 --> 00:06:38,792
If you're finished, may I leave now?

121
00:06:39,040 --> 00:06:41,448
I want to go back to my own circle.

122
00:06:43,536 --> 00:06:44,563
What?

123
00:06:45,718 --> 00:06:47,181
Sure. Go ahead.

124
00:06:52,840 --> 00:06:55,925
What was that?
I thought I was the one landing the punch,

125
00:06:56,293 --> 00:06:58,605
so why do I feel like
I got punched instead?

126
00:07:00,448 --> 00:07:01,741
That woman, seriously.

127
00:07:06,343 --> 00:07:07,707
What? Grades?

128
00:07:10,456 --> 00:07:13,691
If it weren't for my husband,
I'd have torn her apart.

129
00:07:25,959 --> 00:07:26,959
What's wrong?

130
00:07:27,219 --> 00:07:30,416
She seems kind of familiar.

131
00:07:31,859 --> 00:07:33,059
You too?

132
00:07:34,107 --> 00:07:38,136
Come to think of it,
I felt that way the first time I saw her.

133
00:07:39,824 --> 00:07:41,013
How did this happen?

134
00:07:41,700 --> 00:07:44,693
You couldn't even get out of bed,
and now you're suddenly...

135
00:07:44,758 --> 00:07:46,258
She said something earlier.

136
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:50,637
That the person I'm looking for...

137
00:07:51,869 --> 00:07:53,700
must be desperately waiting to see me too.

138
00:07:54,529 --> 00:07:56,512
That one sentence
snapped me right out of it.

139
00:07:57,237 --> 00:07:59,300
It made me realize
this wasn't the time to be lying in bed.

140
00:08:00,147 --> 00:08:03,900
One sentence from her
was more effective than a hundred from me.

141
00:08:04,651 --> 00:08:06,053
What would you like for lunch?

142
00:08:06,875 --> 00:08:10,008
I'll make you a meal myself
for the first time in a while.

143
00:08:10,416 --> 00:08:14,480
Why bother? We can just
have the oxtail soup she brought.

144
00:08:15,104 --> 00:08:16,200
Would you like that?

145
00:08:19,226 --> 00:08:20,993
(Kangsu Construction)

146
00:08:22,280 --> 00:08:23,728
Okay. Here.

147
00:08:24,643 --> 00:08:27,061
We've got some time before lunch.

148
00:08:27,485 --> 00:08:29,568
I'm going around to inspect
the departments, so come with me.

149
00:08:29,971 --> 00:08:30,971
Inspect?

150
00:08:30,971 --> 00:08:33,931
It's partly to boost employee morale.

151
00:08:34,321 --> 00:08:36,216
And besides, I'm going to be Chairman
of Kangsu Group one day.

152
00:08:36,885 --> 00:08:38,275
I should start thinking like an owner.

153
00:08:38,653 --> 00:08:41,832
The Chairman is still very much alive.
You should watch what you say.

154
00:08:42,006 --> 00:08:43,136
There you go again.

155
00:08:43,691 --> 00:08:46,184
Did I say
I was becoming Chairman tomorrow?

156
00:08:46,461 --> 00:08:48,859
I mean someday, in the future.

157
00:08:49,480 --> 00:08:51,100
All right then, let's go.

158
00:08:51,645 --> 00:08:52,645
Open the door.

159
00:08:56,193 --> 00:08:57,193
Hurry up.

160
00:09:00,752 --> 00:09:03,499
So when Joy says things like,
"Please feed me, I'm hungry,"

161
00:09:03,499 --> 00:09:04,869
and makes a request,

162
00:09:05,141 --> 00:09:08,133
the user would place Joy
on the charging dock and recharge it.

163
00:09:09,747 --> 00:09:12,640
I like it. But do we have enough time
before the second round?

164
00:09:13,293 --> 00:09:14,781
We'll just have to push ourselves again.

165
00:09:18,037 --> 00:09:19,557
What's wrong?
Did something get in your eye?

166
00:09:20,152 --> 00:09:21,499
I think so.

167
00:09:23,480 --> 00:09:25,472
Don't rub it. You'll scratch your cornea.

168
00:09:26,024 --> 00:09:27,024
Open your eye.

169
00:09:27,736 --> 00:09:29,397
It stings too much. I can't.

170
00:09:30,232 --> 00:09:33,360
The best thing to do
is to let your tears wash it out.

171
00:09:33,876 --> 00:09:35,483
Maybe think of something sad.

172
00:09:35,688 --> 00:09:39,283
What? Think of something sad?
Are you kidding me?

173
00:09:59,280 --> 00:10:01,315
Why are there only two of you
in the office?

174
00:10:02,339 --> 00:10:04,880
Team One is in a meeting room.

175
00:10:05,304 --> 00:10:07,621
And Assistant Manager Kim from Team Two
is at the archives.

176
00:10:07,789 --> 00:10:08,789
What brings you here?

177
00:10:08,872 --> 00:10:11,589
Nothing special.
Just checking in on the employees.

178
00:10:12,559 --> 00:10:14,659
But don't you think we came in
at a bad time?

179
00:10:15,300 --> 00:10:16,523
You two seem awfully cozy.

180
00:10:17,364 --> 00:10:19,997
Not at all.
We were discussing the Joy program.

181
00:10:22,077 --> 00:10:23,667
Let's move on to another department.

182
00:10:25,096 --> 00:10:26,096
Yeah, let's do that.

183
00:10:26,418 --> 00:10:28,491
But why is it so hot in here?

184
00:10:28,931 --> 00:10:31,424
Should we turn the air conditioning up?

185
00:10:31,424 --> 00:10:32,659
Make it cooler?

186
00:10:35,712 --> 00:10:38,845
I think the CEO got the wrong idea.
What do we do?

187
00:10:39,009 --> 00:10:40,009
How's your eye?

188
00:10:40,180 --> 00:10:41,933
I think it's better now.

189
00:10:43,613 --> 00:10:45,513
- Let's continue.
- Okay.

190
00:10:46,691 --> 00:10:49,509
Besides charging,
when we upgrade the system,

191
00:10:49,509 --> 00:10:52,725
it might be good
if users could unlock more features...

192
00:10:52,725 --> 00:10:54,333
the more they take care of Joy.

193
00:10:59,739 --> 00:11:02,320
So?
How was witnessing the scene firsthand?

194
00:11:02,877 --> 00:11:04,277
Witnessing what scene?

195
00:11:05,021 --> 00:11:07,203
I'll ask my daughter directly.

196
00:11:07,848 --> 00:11:09,635
Don't bother. Just leave them alone.

197
00:11:10,164 --> 00:11:12,435
Young people fool around like that
and then, before you know it...

198
00:11:15,700 --> 00:11:18,673
What I mean is,
Gyeol's going back to the U.S. soon.

199
00:11:18,673 --> 00:11:20,725
Do you really think it's serious?

200
00:11:21,316 --> 00:11:23,901
Just leave them be.
They'll sort it out themselves.

201
00:11:26,261 --> 00:11:30,315
Well, Manager Seo's the one left
chasing a chicken she can't catch.

202
00:11:31,259 --> 00:11:32,259
Sorry?

203
00:11:34,371 --> 00:11:36,499
- What are you doing? Open the door.
- Yes, sir.

204
00:11:39,056 --> 00:11:40,549
Is this really the best you've got
for the Joy proposal?

205
00:11:40,987 --> 00:11:43,005
How is it different
from the first-round version?

206
00:11:44,283 --> 00:11:46,371
The IoT integration technology...

207
00:11:46,371 --> 00:11:50,123
was already developed previously,

208
00:11:51,349 --> 00:11:55,648
and it acts as a perfect assistant,

209
00:11:56,543 --> 00:11:58,155
providing everything the user needs...

210
00:12:00,978 --> 00:12:02,643
Everyone's working hard.

211
00:12:03,264 --> 00:12:06,664
As expected,
Team One is on a whole different level.

212
00:12:07,005 --> 00:12:08,133
What brings you here,
all the way to the meeting room?

213
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:12,099
Just making the rounds
and encouraging the staff.

214
00:12:14,085 --> 00:12:17,563
So, can I expect Team One
to win the second round?

215
00:12:22,788 --> 00:12:23,788
What I mean is,

216
00:12:23,997 --> 00:12:27,453
I want you to do your best
regardless of the result.

217
00:12:28,067 --> 00:12:30,331
Right. And if you need anything,

218
00:12:30,928 --> 00:12:32,435
just let me know.

219
00:12:32,637 --> 00:12:34,067
All right. You can do it.

220
00:12:34,780 --> 00:12:36,131
Okay, I'll get going.

221
00:12:37,100 --> 00:12:38,395
Open the door.

222
00:12:43,859 --> 00:12:45,621
I get the feeling...

223
00:12:45,621 --> 00:12:47,664
the CEO is rooting for Team One more.

224
00:12:48,650 --> 00:12:49,835
I think so too, Chief Ko.

225
00:12:50,395 --> 00:12:51,912
And I think we will win
the second round as well...

226
00:12:51,912 --> 00:12:54,805
That is,
if you come up with a version of Joy...

227
00:12:55,252 --> 00:12:57,376
that's more distinctive
than Ms. Cho Eun Ae's.

228
00:12:58,768 --> 00:13:01,259
Okay. By the next meeting,

229
00:13:01,532 --> 00:13:03,643
I'll make sure
the distinction is crystal clear...

230
00:13:06,732 --> 00:13:07,732
Yes.

231
00:13:08,690 --> 00:13:09,690
What do you mean?

232
00:13:09,773 --> 00:13:12,100
You think there's some issue
between CEO Ko and Team Manager Ko?

233
00:13:12,669 --> 00:13:14,493
I've wondered about it for a while.

234
00:13:15,080 --> 00:13:17,667
The way he treats Chief Ko
and Team Manager Ko feels...

235
00:13:18,341 --> 00:13:20,533
More than anything, the brothers
are competing against each other,

236
00:13:21,172 --> 00:13:24,072
yet he keeps seeming biased
toward Chief Ko's team.

237
00:13:25,242 --> 00:13:28,088
Well, Chief Ko is the eldest son.

238
00:13:28,939 --> 00:13:31,864
And CEO Ko has never been good
at hiding what he thinks.

239
00:13:33,661 --> 00:13:35,744
Maybe, but still...

240
00:13:37,144 --> 00:13:40,979
Well, Manager Seo's the one left
chasing a chicken she can't catch.

241
00:13:42,856 --> 00:13:45,672
Right, does Manager Seo have a boyfriend?

242
00:13:46,867 --> 00:13:48,965
Not yet. Why?

243
00:13:49,429 --> 00:13:53,448
Earlier, CEO Ko mentioned
Manager Seo and Team Manager Ko.

244
00:13:55,059 --> 00:13:58,531
The truth is, my daughter has had a crush
on Team Manager Ko for over ten years.

245
00:13:59,156 --> 00:14:01,307
And Chief Ko is tangled up in it too,
which makes things complicated.

246
00:14:02,047 --> 00:14:03,047
What?

247
00:14:04,179 --> 00:14:07,523
No wonder things felt strange...

248
00:14:07,689 --> 00:14:09,125
when we all had lunch together
the other day.

249
00:14:11,196 --> 00:14:14,061
I need to stop by somewhere during lunch.
See you later.

250
00:14:15,043 --> 00:14:16,600
All right. Have a good trip.

251
00:14:32,368 --> 00:14:33,965
Something small and shiny?

252
00:14:34,441 --> 00:14:35,974
Seung Wu was saying earlier...

253
00:14:36,435 --> 00:14:38,805
that I should get your mom a gift
that would really move her.

254
00:14:39,448 --> 00:14:43,357
But I have no idea what that might be.

255
00:14:44,811 --> 00:14:47,888
It means jewelry. Something like diamonds.

256
00:14:48,429 --> 00:14:49,429
Diamonds?

257
00:15:13,209 --> 00:15:14,209
Mr. Seo.

258
00:15:15,069 --> 00:15:16,683
Chief Ko.

259
00:15:16,837 --> 00:15:17,873
What brings you here?

260
00:15:18,024 --> 00:15:20,333
Shopping for a gift for your wife?

261
00:15:20,635 --> 00:15:24,317
Something like that. What about you?

262
00:15:30,148 --> 00:15:31,248
Thank you for waiting.

263
00:15:34,948 --> 00:15:36,248
You're going to propose to Seung Ri?

264
00:15:36,851 --> 00:15:38,751
I should've talked to you first.
I'm sorry.

265
00:15:39,387 --> 00:15:42,387
I'm planning to do it soon,
and I'd appreciate your help.

266
00:15:44,489 --> 00:15:45,741
Has Seung Ri opened her heart to you?

267
00:15:47,072 --> 00:15:50,792
If not,
I think proposing would be rushing things.

268
00:15:52,323 --> 00:15:55,227
There are stages to everything.

269
00:15:55,643 --> 00:15:58,480
That's why I've respected her feelings
and waited all this time.

270
00:15:59,764 --> 00:16:01,851
But I'm going to take action now.

271
00:16:03,469 --> 00:16:05,769
I don't know
if I should be telling you this, but...

272
00:16:06,584 --> 00:16:09,720
Gyeol has recently fallen for someone.

273
00:16:10,224 --> 00:16:12,325
- And Seung Ri knows about it.
- What?

274
00:16:12,995 --> 00:16:16,997
I don't intend to keep watching her suffer
because of Gyeol.

275
00:16:18,299 --> 00:16:19,299
Who does Gyeol like?

276
00:16:23,160 --> 00:16:26,467
Don't tell me it's Ms. Cho Eun Ae.

277
00:16:27,853 --> 00:16:31,112
Yes. And she likes Gyeol too.

278
00:16:35,445 --> 00:16:38,545
I'm going to make Seung Ri happy,
no matter what.

279
00:16:42,805 --> 00:16:44,957
Bit Na,
did you have fun at kindergarten today?

280
00:16:45,171 --> 00:16:47,304
- Yeah.
- Who did you play with?

281
00:16:47,491 --> 00:16:49,248
- Ye Eun.
- Ye Eun?

282
00:16:50,685 --> 00:16:51,685
It's Mom!

283
00:16:52,573 --> 00:16:54,923
- Bit Na.
- Mom!

284
00:16:55,161 --> 00:16:56,664
Mom!

285
00:16:58,159 --> 00:17:00,021
- Have you been good, sweetheart?
- Yeah.

286
00:17:02,600 --> 00:17:05,643
How come you're here, Cho Rong?

287
00:17:06,293 --> 00:17:08,926
I'm the one with the most free time,
so I pick Bit Na up sometimes.

288
00:17:10,259 --> 00:17:11,512
Thank you, Cho Rong.

289
00:17:12,488 --> 00:17:16,304
I need to talk to Bit Na for a minute,
so could you...

290
00:17:16,976 --> 00:17:19,459
Sure.
I'll just head home since you're here.

291
00:17:19,459 --> 00:17:22,787
Actually, I have to leave again soon.

292
00:17:23,219 --> 00:17:26,123
Could you wait a little while?

293
00:17:26,485 --> 00:17:28,616
Of course. I'll be over there.

294
00:17:29,439 --> 00:17:30,439
Okay.

295
00:17:35,712 --> 00:17:37,373
- Have you been good?
- Yeah.

296
00:17:46,275 --> 00:17:47,275
Dad.

297
00:17:50,237 --> 00:17:51,237
Bit Na.

298
00:17:52,416 --> 00:17:54,325
Listen carefully
to what Mom's about to say.

299
00:17:56,056 --> 00:18:00,093
You and Dad are going to stay
at Grandma's house for a while.

300
00:18:00,983 --> 00:18:02,383
What about you, Mom?

301
00:18:03,531 --> 00:18:07,261
Mom's very busy with work right now,

302
00:18:09,064 --> 00:18:10,697
so I don't think I'll be able to see you
for a while.

303
00:18:10,950 --> 00:18:12,584
For how long?

304
00:18:15,664 --> 00:18:18,947
Grandpa, Grandma, Dad, and your aunts...

305
00:18:19,229 --> 00:18:21,360
all love you very much, don't they?

306
00:18:23,445 --> 00:18:27,145
So you'll be okay, right?

307
00:18:30,289 --> 00:18:34,539
But I want to go to our house
with you and Dad.

308
00:18:43,608 --> 00:18:44,755
I'm sorry, Bit Na.

309
00:18:48,459 --> 00:18:51,856
And can you keep it a secret...

310
00:18:52,433 --> 00:18:56,112
that I came here today?

311
00:18:56,653 --> 00:19:01,267
Why?
So you could surprise them with apples?

312
00:19:02,273 --> 00:19:04,651
- What?
- Dad said so.

313
00:19:05,183 --> 00:19:08,555
He said not to tell them
because you're planning a surprise.

314
00:19:11,300 --> 00:19:12,300
Yes.

315
00:19:13,955 --> 00:19:16,864
That's right. A surprise.

316
00:19:18,559 --> 00:19:20,205
Come here. Let me give you a hug.

317
00:19:29,727 --> 00:19:32,480
Mom, why are you crying? Don't cry.

318
00:19:32,997 --> 00:19:35,920
When you cry, it makes me sad too.

319
00:19:39,152 --> 00:19:41,384
My sweet girl, don't cry, Bit Na.

320
00:19:42,003 --> 00:19:44,837
Once I find all the apples,

321
00:19:45,368 --> 00:19:47,728
I'll come see you again, okay?

322
00:19:49,018 --> 00:19:50,931
So no more tears.

323
00:20:09,549 --> 00:20:11,611
What's wrong? Don't you like tteokbokki?

324
00:20:12,627 --> 00:20:13,909
You enjoyed it last time.

325
00:20:14,643 --> 00:20:17,760
I don't want any. I'm not hungry.

326
00:20:18,877 --> 00:20:22,733
Why? Did something upset you?

327
00:20:23,568 --> 00:20:25,832
I'm sleepy, Grandma.

328
00:20:26,459 --> 00:20:29,059
Sleepy? Do you want to take a nap?

329
00:20:29,544 --> 00:20:30,544
Yes.

330
00:20:31,461 --> 00:20:34,795
All right. Go lie down then.

331
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:46,533
(Eldest Son)

332
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:53,000
The person you are trying to reach
is unavailable. Please leave a message...

333
00:20:53,175 --> 00:20:54,775
He must be teaching.

334
00:20:59,833 --> 00:21:00,833
(Ji Seon)

335
00:21:06,900 --> 00:21:09,536
Jazz dance...

336
00:21:09,845 --> 00:21:13,633
Jazz dance...

337
00:21:15,632 --> 00:21:17,203
Is something bothering you?

338
00:21:17,952 --> 00:21:21,363
You've been deep in thought all this time.

339
00:21:23,410 --> 00:21:24,410
No. It's nothing.

340
00:21:25,792 --> 00:21:27,480
Grandma, Eun Hyeong's family...

341
00:21:27,580 --> 00:21:28,795
What about Eun Hyeong's family?

342
00:21:29,965 --> 00:21:30,965
Never mind.

343
00:21:30,965 --> 00:21:34,304
Hey, if you start something,
you finish it.

344
00:21:34,304 --> 00:21:35,933
Don't leave it hanging.

345
00:21:37,192 --> 00:21:40,184
Cho Rong,
did Bit Na say anything on the way home?

346
00:21:41,361 --> 00:21:42,461
No. Why?

347
00:21:43,339 --> 00:21:44,640
She seems completely drained.

348
00:21:44,640 --> 00:21:47,288
She didn't even want a snack
and went straight to sleep.

349
00:21:48,948 --> 00:21:51,015
Did she get into a fight with a friend
at kindergarten?

350
00:21:51,568 --> 00:21:54,451
No. We played hopscotch on the way back.

351
00:21:54,451 --> 00:21:56,187
Maybe she's upset
because she lost to me over and over.

352
00:21:56,187 --> 00:21:57,931
You little rascal.

353
00:21:57,931 --> 00:22:00,997
You seriously beat
a seven-year-old that badly?

354
00:22:01,334 --> 00:22:03,934
She must've been crushed.

355
00:22:04,767 --> 00:22:06,395
Yeah, I guess I messed up.

356
00:22:06,797 --> 00:22:09,917
Really? If that's all it is, then fine.

357
00:22:10,232 --> 00:22:12,277
- I'll get going.
- All right.

358
00:22:14,064 --> 00:22:15,813
Wait, Ms. Cho.

359
00:22:16,467 --> 00:22:19,848
So the heroine jumps off the rooftop?

360
00:22:20,136 --> 00:22:21,547
Who said she jumps?

361
00:22:21,547 --> 00:22:23,701
I said she's conflicted about jumping.

362
00:22:24,088 --> 00:22:26,707
Then the male lead comes
and pulls her back.

363
00:22:27,567 --> 00:22:29,915
Ms. Cho, our heroine...

364
00:22:29,979 --> 00:22:33,011
is a doctor who saves lives. A doctor.

365
00:22:33,544 --> 00:22:35,248
Do you think someone like that...

366
00:22:35,248 --> 00:22:37,771
should treat her own life so lightly?

367
00:22:37,771 --> 00:22:39,336
Who's treating it lightly?

368
00:22:39,336 --> 00:22:42,139
She's just burned out
after pushing herself too hard.

369
00:22:42,700 --> 00:22:45,416
Even so, isn't that a bit...

370
00:22:45,416 --> 00:22:48,387
too extreme a way to show burnout?

371
00:22:48,687 --> 00:22:49,687
Listen.

372
00:22:50,061 --> 00:22:53,456
I thought we agreed not to interfere
in each other's territory.

373
00:22:53,962 --> 00:22:55,171
I do the writing, you do the art.

374
00:22:56,400 --> 00:23:00,411
I'm officially involved
with "The ER Witch" too.

375
00:23:00,605 --> 00:23:02,760
If I can't agree with the writing,

376
00:23:02,989 --> 00:23:04,968
how am I supposed to draw it properly?

377
00:23:09,800 --> 00:23:10,976
Hello, Hye Ji.

378
00:23:12,157 --> 00:23:13,973
Yes, I'm at the studio.

379
00:23:14,841 --> 00:23:18,211
I'm usually only here at night,
but I had a meeting today.

380
00:23:20,308 --> 00:23:22,824
Of course. Come by anytime.

381
00:23:24,693 --> 00:23:28,040
Actually, no. Not anytime.

382
00:23:28,280 --> 00:23:30,580
I'll set a time and contact you.

383
00:23:31,125 --> 00:23:33,400
Okay. Bye.

384
00:23:35,795 --> 00:23:39,117
Who were you talking to just now?
Don't tell me it was my friend, Oh Hye Ji.

385
00:23:40,259 --> 00:23:42,773
You're even ruder than you look.

386
00:23:43,189 --> 00:23:44,941
Listening in on other people's calls.

387
00:23:45,247 --> 00:23:48,811
Who was listening in?
You were talking right in front of me.

388
00:23:49,764 --> 00:23:51,661
But how does Hye Ji have your number?

389
00:23:52,316 --> 00:23:53,916
I never gave it to her.

390
00:23:55,376 --> 00:23:56,793
She picked me up.

391
00:23:56,793 --> 00:23:58,101
What? Picked you up?

392
00:23:58,900 --> 00:24:00,283
She asked for my number.

393
00:24:00,348 --> 00:24:02,027
What? Is there a problem?

394
00:24:02,728 --> 00:24:04,456
Oh Hye Ji has completely lost it.

395
00:24:06,401 --> 00:24:07,901
The meeting's over, so you should leave.

396
00:24:08,109 --> 00:24:11,352
It's my time now. Day, me. Night, you.

397
00:24:14,500 --> 00:24:16,500
Looks like you haven't read it
very carefully yet.

398
00:24:16,725 --> 00:24:18,165
Meeting days are exempt, remember?

399
00:24:19,177 --> 00:24:21,171
Seriously, are you a goldfish or what?

400
00:24:23,093 --> 00:24:24,520
Stop doing that.

401
00:24:24,600 --> 00:24:28,584
What? I can't move my lips now?

402
00:24:43,337 --> 00:24:44,337
Is nobody home?

403
00:25:00,311 --> 00:25:03,179
Honey, I'm home.

404
00:25:05,957 --> 00:25:06,957
I'm starving.

405
00:25:08,200 --> 00:25:10,605
Aren't we eating?

406
00:25:13,493 --> 00:25:15,576
Do I look like your personal cook?

407
00:25:16,037 --> 00:25:17,840
Am I a restaurant lady?

408
00:25:25,400 --> 00:25:27,851
What's this?

409
00:25:28,600 --> 00:25:31,600
What do you think? It's a gift.

410
00:25:32,500 --> 00:25:34,757
A gift for me?

411
00:25:35,643 --> 00:25:37,276
(Kangsu Construction)

412
00:25:41,535 --> 00:25:43,235
You're still here, Manager Seo?

413
00:25:43,564 --> 00:25:45,397
I was just about to leave.
Are you here alone?

414
00:25:48,129 --> 00:25:51,429
Yes. Everyone else left earlier,
but I still had some work to finish.

415
00:25:52,027 --> 00:25:54,260
It's late. Don't stay too long.
I'm heading out.

416
00:25:55,117 --> 00:25:56,650
Okay. Good night.

417
00:26:11,045 --> 00:26:12,612
Did you forget something, Manager Seo?

418
00:26:14,977 --> 00:26:17,610
I thought you'd already left,
Team Manager.

419
00:26:17,925 --> 00:26:19,837
No.
I had a meeting with the Finance Team...

420
00:26:19,837 --> 00:26:21,877
about the second round. It just ended.

421
00:26:22,667 --> 00:26:24,567
I'm leaving now too, so let's go together.

422
00:26:24,567 --> 00:26:25,617
I told you.

423
00:26:25,617 --> 00:26:28,624
I'm finishing the Joy upgrade tonight
no matter what.

424
00:26:30,405 --> 00:26:32,005
Do it at home.

425
00:26:32,005 --> 00:26:34,141
Do you really have to make me worry
like this?

426
00:26:34,864 --> 00:26:38,171
Sorry? I don't remember asking you
to worry about me.

427
00:26:38,779 --> 00:26:42,277
I've gotten so used to commuting
by scooter...

428
00:26:42,553 --> 00:26:43,953
that I have no desire
to take the bus anymore.

429
00:26:44,284 --> 00:26:45,389
So get up already.

430
00:26:45,784 --> 00:26:47,171
Come on. Get up.

431
00:26:47,975 --> 00:26:50,108
Anyone listening would think
the scooter belongs to you.

432
00:26:50,754 --> 00:26:53,288
And what am I, your personal chauffeur?

433
00:26:57,296 --> 00:26:58,296
Let's go home.

434
00:26:59,040 --> 00:27:00,520
Starting today,
you're paying transportation costs.

435
00:27:00,629 --> 00:27:02,832
Do you even know
how expensive gas is these days?

436
00:27:02,832 --> 00:27:04,952
Why would I need to know that?

437
00:27:05,072 --> 00:27:06,272
Come on. Let's go, Driver Cho.

438
00:27:06,531 --> 00:27:08,499
Driver Cho? Seriously?

439
00:27:08,653 --> 00:27:11,220
I'm starving. Let's hurry home
and eat a home-cooked meal.

440
00:27:16,533 --> 00:27:18,213
You're taking forever.

441
00:27:18,312 --> 00:27:20,587
- Just wait a second.
- Come on, Driver Cho.

442
00:27:21,329 --> 00:27:22,787
- Careful.
- Here we go.

443
00:27:23,000 --> 00:27:24,000
Okay.

444
00:27:32,981 --> 00:27:34,773
Seo Seung Ri, what are you doing?

445
00:27:43,208 --> 00:27:44,208
It came early.

446
00:27:44,709 --> 00:27:45,709
What's that?

447
00:27:46,593 --> 00:27:49,349
If you're curious, watch "Any Questions."

448
00:27:51,120 --> 00:27:54,371
Anyway, it's late.
Do you think your mom left dinner for us?

449
00:27:54,371 --> 00:27:57,053
Don't worry.
No matter how mad my mom gets,

450
00:27:57,053 --> 00:27:58,353
she believes in feeding people
before scolding them.

451
00:27:59,267 --> 00:28:02,043
As long as we have rice,
I can whip up whatever you're craving.

452
00:28:02,867 --> 00:28:03,867
Yes, Chef.

453
00:28:04,951 --> 00:28:06,349
Wait for me, Driver Cho.

454
00:28:29,100 --> 00:28:30,700
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
